2b\",null,{\"src\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-ijic-public/journals/1/journalThumbnail_en_US.jpg\",\"alt\":\"thumbnail image\",\"className\":\"ldKigU dphVp\",\"fill\":true}]}]\na9:[\"$\",\"$L30\",null,{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"href\":\"/en/articles/10.5334/ijic.ICIC25630\",\"locale\":\"$undefined\",\"localeCookie\":\"$2d:props:localeCookie\",\"className\":\"wzdQU gsjAMe jutHam kFYpjC ifFlTd QKtVo\",\"children\":\"Real World Examples: Actioning Person Centred Care and Self-Management\"}]\naa:[\"$\",\"$L30\",\"link0\",{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"href\":\"/en/180/volume/26/issue/S1\",\"locale\":\"$undefined\",\"localeCookie\":\"$2d:props:localeCookie\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",\"volume0\",{\"title\":\"Volume 26\",\"children\":26}],\"(\",[\"$\",\"span\",\"issue0\",{\"title\":\"Issue S1\",\"children\":\"S1\"}],\")\"]}]\nab:[\"$\",\"$L30\",\"link0\",{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"href\":\"/en/180/volume/26/issue/S1\",\"locale\":\"$undefined\",\"localeCookie\":\"$2d:props:localeCookie\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",\"volume0\",{\"title\":\"Volume 26\",\"children\":26}],\"(\",[\"$\",\"span\",\"issue0\",{\"title\":\"Issue S1\",\"children\":\"S1\"}],\")\"]}]\nac:[\"$\",\"$L30\",null,{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"href\":\"/en/articles/10.5334/ijic.ICIC25629\",\"locale\":\"$undefined\",\"localeCookie\":\"$2d:props:localeCookie\",\"tabIndex\":-1,\"className\":\"jTWvec cGFOJB fCxUcq fCxQKC\",\"aria-hidden\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L2b\",null,{\"src\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-ijic-public/journals/1/journalThumbnail_en_US.jpg\",\"alt\":\"thumbnail image\",\"className\":\"ldKigU dphVp\",\"fill\":true}]}]\nad:[\"$\",\"$L30\",null,{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"href\":\"/en/articles/10.5334/ijic.ICIC25629\",\"locale\":\"$undefined\",\"localeCookie\":\"$2d:props:localeCookie\",\"className\":\"wzdQU gsjAMe jutHam kFYpjC ifFlTd QKtVo\",\"children\":\"Putting the ‘to’ in Participatory Research to Action: Research and service-design collaboration on sustainable solutions for integrated mental health care\"}]\nae:[\"$\",\"$L30\",\"link0\",{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"href\":\"/en/180/volume/26/issue/S1\",\"locale\":\"$undefined\",\"localeCookie\":\"$2d:props:localeCookie\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",\"volume0\",{\"title\":\"Volume 26\",\"children\":26}],\"(\",[\"$\",\"span\",\"issue0\",{\"title\":\"Iss"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"ue S1\",\"children\":\"S1\"}],\")\"]}]\naf:[\"$\",\"$L30\",\"link0\",{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"href\":\"/en/180/volume/26/issue/S1\",\"locale\":\"$undefined\",\"localeCookie\":\"$2d:props:localeCookie\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",\"volume0\",{\"title\":\"Volume 26\",\"children\":26}],\"(\",[\"$\",\"span\",\"issue0\",{\"title\":\"Issue S1\",\"children\":\"S1\"}],\")\"]}]\nb0:[\"$\",\"$L30\",null,{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"href\":\"/en/articles/10.5334/ijic.ICIC25628\",\"locale\":\"$undefined\",\"localeCookie\":\"$2d:props:localeCookie\",\"tabIndex\":-1,\"className\":\"jTWvec cGFOJB fCxUcq fCxQKC\",\"aria-hidden\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L2b\",null,{\"src\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-ijic-public/journals/1/journalThumbnail_en_US.jpg\",\"alt\":\"thumbnail image\",\"className\":\"ldKigU dphVp\",\"fill\":true}]}]\nb1:[\"$\",\"$L30\",null,{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"href\":\"/en/articles/10.5334/ijic.ICIC25628\",\"locale\":\"$undefined\",\"localeCookie\":\"$2d:props:localeCookie\",\"className\":\"wzdQU gsjAMe jutHam kFYpjC ifFlTd QKtVo\",\"children\":\"Leveraging GPT Models for Efficient Integrated Care Projects Planning: An Interactive Workshop\"}]\nb2:[\"$\",\"$L30\",\"link0\",{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"href\":\"/en/180/volume/26/issue/S1\",\"locale\":\"$undefined\",\"localeCookie\":\"$2d:props:localeCookie\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",\"volume0\",{\"title\":\"Volume 26\",\"children\":26}],\"(\",[\"$\",\"span\",\"issue0\",{\"title\":\"Issue S1\",\"children\":\"S1\"}],\")\"]}]\nb3:[\"$\",\"$L30\",\"link0\",{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"href\":\"/en/180/volume/26/issue/S1\",\"locale\":\"$undefined\",\"localeCookie\":\"$2d:props:localeCookie\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",\"volume0\",{\"title\":\"Volume 26\",\"children\":26}],\"(\",[\"$\",\"span\",\"issue0\",{\"title\":\"Issue S1\",\"children\":\"S1\"}],\")\"]}]\nb7:T3720,"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"\u003ch2\u003eFocus and Scope\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSince its inception in 2000 the International Journal of Integrated Care has documented the trends, developments and newest findings in the research, policy and practice of integrated care. As its subject matter has continuously evolved over the years, so have the articles we publish reflected the growing understanding of what integrated care is and what it isn’t. Some of the key learnings over the years have been that, while there are some common building blocks and elements, which are essential for integrated care, ultimately all frameworks and models need to be contextualized to local needs and resources. This contextualization should ideally happen with wide community and professional involvement.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eRead the full \u003ca href=\"/about/aims-and-scope\"\u003eAims and Scope\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003ePublication Frequency\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eContinuous publishing and archived issues\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTo publish articles on a continuous basis means that they enter the \u003ca title=\"blocked::http://www.ijic.org/index.php/ijic/issue/current\" href=\"/issue/archive/\" target=\"_self\"\u003e\u003cem title=\"blocked::http://www.ijic.org/index.php/ijic/issue/current\"\u003ecurrent issue\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e as soon as they are ready to publish. IJIC then archives its articles within 4 issues: Jan-March; April-June; July-Sept; Oct-Dec.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIJIC often publishes groups of papers related to a theme in \u003cstrong\u003eSpecial Editions\u003c/strong\u003e and also develops \u003cstrong\u003eConference Supplements\u003c/strong\u003e to publish the abstracts from academic congresses. Special Editions normally run for a year and are archived as annual editions.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003eOpen Access Policy\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis journal provides immediate open access to its content on the principle that making research freely available to the public supports a greater global exchange of knowledge. There is no embargo on the journal’s publications. Submission and acceptance dates, along with publication dates, are made available on the PDF format for each paper.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAuthors of articles published remain the copyright holders and grant third parties the right to use, reproduce, and share the article according to the \u003ca href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eCreative Commons\u003c/a\u003e license agreement.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAuthors are encouraged to publish their data in recommended repositories. For a list of generic and subject specific repositories that meet our peer review criteria, see \u003ca href=\"http://oad.simmons.edu/oadwiki/Data_repositories\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003ehere\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003eArchiving Policy\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis journal utilizes the \u003ca href=\"http://lockss.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eLOCKSS\u003c/a\u003e system to create a distributed archiving system among participating libraries and permits those libraries to create permanent archives of the journal for purposes of preservation and restoration.\u003c!-- CLOCKSS system has permission to ingest, preserve, and serve this Archival Unit --\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003eWhy publish in IJIC?\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIJIC can offer you the expertise, experience and networks of a distinguished multidisciplinary group of researchers and policy analysts. We also offer authors the following advantages:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul class=\"list\"\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eNo time lost!\u003c/strong\u003e - Online publishing allows IJIC to depart from the traditional journal structure of monthly or quarterly issues. Submissions are accepted at all times and are peer reviewed and published on a continuous basis.This means that your work doesn't lie on a shelf waiting for publication. The world can access your work rapidly.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSize!\u003c/strong\u003e - Articles may be longer and contain more tables than would be permitted in a hard copy journal, although every article is evaluated on the ratio of number of words to news value.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMulti-media!\u003c/strong\u003e - We welcome full-colour photos, audio material and video footage for illustrating the message and content of an article.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePubMed Central!\u003c/strong\u003e - All articles published in the International Journal Of Integrated Care will appear in the database of PubMed Central and consequently in the PubMed search engine\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCoverage in Web of Science (SSCI and SCI) and Scopus!\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003eFacts and figures\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe total number of \u003cstrong\u003efull text views and downloads\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003efrom PubMed Central\u003c/strong\u003e during 2024 was \u003cstrong\u003e635,207\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn 2024 there were \u003cstrong\u003e242,000 \u003c/strong\u003evisits to the IJIC website and \u003cstrong\u003e223,000\u003c/strong\u003e unique page views.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003eIndexing, Archiving and Dissemination\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUbiquity is committed to making content discoverable and accessible through indexing services. As such all content is archived around the world to ensure long-term availability.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUbiquity supports open and transparent practices in scholarly research and is a signatory of \u003ca href=\"https://sfdora.org/\"\u003eThe Declaration on Research Assessment (DORA)\u003c/a\u003e, a global initiative to improve the ways in which researchers and the outputs of scholarly research are evaluated. In accordance with DORA, Ubiquity makes available a range of article and journal-level metrics to avoid over-reliance on any single assessment tool.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOur journals use \u003ca href=\"https://metrics.operas-eu.org/\"\u003eOPERAS metrics\u003c/a\u003e - an open source platform that Ubiquity has helped develop as part of the \u003ca href=\"https://operas.hypotheses.org/projects/hirmeos\"\u003eHIRMEOS project\u003c/a\u003e, originating from the European Union's Horizon 2020 research and innovation programme. OPERAS metrics provides a comprehensive and transparent mechanism for collecting and aggregating article usage metrics.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eJournal statistics (including submission numbers, the acceptance rate, and turnaround times) are provided and updated annually.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr /\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eEvaluation and Impact\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eJournal Citation Indicator\u003c/strong\u003e: 0.78 - \u003cspan data-sheets-root=\"1\"\u003e80/185\u003c/span\u003e (2024)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eJournal Impact Factor\u003c/strong\u003e: 2.6 - 70/185 (2024)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eScopus CiteScore\u003c/strong\u003e: 4.5 - 258/1497 Sociology and Political Science (2024)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eScimago H-index\u003c/strong\u003e: 47 (2024)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eScimago Journal Rank (SJR)\u003c/strong\u003e: 0.1106 (2024)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003chr /\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eIndexing and Discoverability\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe journal is indexed by the following services:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOpen Access\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://www.base-search.net/\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eBASE search, Bielefeld Academic Search Engine\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://journalfinder.chronoshub.io/?q=%221568-4156%22\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eChronosHub\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://oversea.cnki.net/index/\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eCNKI\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.dimensions.ai/\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eDimensions\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://www.doaj.org/\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eDirectory of Open Access Journals (DOAJ)\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://ezb.uni-regensburg.de/index.phtml?bibid=AAAAA\u0026amp;colors=7\u0026amp;lang=en\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eElectronic Journals Library (University of Regensburg)\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://scholar.google.com/\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eGoogle scholar\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://www.medexplorer.com/subcategory.cfm?Nav=subcategory\u0026amp;category=News_Publications\u0026amp;subcat1=Online%20Journals\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eMedExplorer\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://oaister.on.worldcat.org/oclc/1453339046\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eOAister\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://explore.openaire.eu/search/publication?pid=10.5334%2Fijic.155\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eOpenAIRE\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/journals/229/\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003ePubMed Central\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003e (included in The PMC Open Access Subset)\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://europepmc.org/journals/800/\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003ePubMed Central Europe\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://www.spandp.net/\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eSocial Policy and Practice\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSubscription databases\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.bdslive.com/\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eBDS Bibliographic Data Services\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.cengage.com/\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eCengage Learning\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.ebsco.com/products/ebsco-knowledge-services\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eEBSCO (Host and Knowledge Base)\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.exlibrisgroup.com/\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eEx Libris\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://jgateplus.com/home/\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eJ-Gate\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.oclc.org/en/home.html\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eOCLC\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.scopus.com/sourceid/21100255082\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eScopus\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://about.proquest.com/en/products-services/Ulrichsweb\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eUlrich's Periodicals Directory\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.webofscience.com/wos/\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eWeb of Science JCR Science Edition and Social Sciences Edition\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLibrary catalogues\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://discover.libraryhub.jisc.ac.uk/\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eJISC Library Hub Discover\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://www.sudoc.fr/151978816\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eSUDOC, Catalogue of resources at all the university libraries in France\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://www.worldcat.org/\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eWorldcat (OCLC), global catalog of library collections\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://zdb-katalog.de/index.xhtml\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eZDB, Catalogue of resources at all the university libraries in Germany\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAdditionally, the journal is registered with \u003ca href=\"https://openpolicyfinder.jisc.ac.uk/id/publication/31635\"\u003eOpen Policy Finder\u003c/a\u003e, and all article metadata and references are deposited with \u003ca href=\"https://www.crossref.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eCrossref\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAs the journal grows, additional indexes will be added. If the journal is not indexed by your preferred service, please \u003ca href=\"/contact/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003econtact us\u003c/a\u003e or alternatively by making an indexing request directly with the service.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003eArchiving\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTo ensure permanency of all publications, this journal also utilises \u003ca href=\"http://www.clockss.org\"\u003eCLOCKSS\u003c/a\u003e, and \u003ca href=\"http://www.lockss.org/\"\u003eLOCKSS\u003c/a\u003e archiving systems to create permanent archives for the purposes of preservation and restoration.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn addition, the journal is available for harvesting via \u003ca href=\"http://www.openarchives.org/pmh/\"\u003eOAI-PMH\u003c/a\u003e. \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003c!-- CLOCKSS system has permission to ingest, preserve, and serve this Archival Unit --\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003eJournal statistics\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCore journal statistics for the 2024 volume (excluding conference issues):\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ctable style=\"width: 90%;\"\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSubmissions received\u003csup\u003e1\u003c/sup\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e232\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eReviews requested\u003csup\u003e2\u003c/sup\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e773\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eReviews received\u003csup\u003e3\u003c/sup\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e182\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eTotal Rejections\u003csup\u003e4\u003c/sup\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e128\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e...of which, Desk rejects\u003csup\u003e5\u003c/sup\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e118\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eAcceptances\u003csup\u003e6\u003c/sup\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e87\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eAcceptance rate\u003csup\u003e7\u003c/sup\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e40.47%\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eTime from submission to publication\u003csup\u003e8\u003c/sup\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e194 days\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDefinitions\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\u003csup\u003e1\u003c/sup\u003eNumber of new articles received by the journal\u003cbr /\u003e\u003csup\u003e2\u003c/sup\u003eNumber of peer review invitation emails that were sent out\u003cbr /\u003e\u003csup\u003e3\u003c/sup\u003eNumber of completed peer review reports received\u003cbr /\u003e\u003csup\u003e4\u003c/sup\u003eTotal number of articles rejected (including desk rejects)\u003cbr /\u003e\u003csup\u003e5\u003c/sup\u003eNumber of articles rejected prior to peer review\u003cbr /\u003e\u003csup\u003e6\u003c/sup\u003eNumber of articles that received a 'Accept for publication' decision\u003cbr /\u003e\u003csup\u003e7\u003c/sup\u003eNumber of acceptances, as a percentage, against the total number of final decisions\u003cbr /\u003e\u003csup\u003e8\u003c/sup\u003e'Mean' average from submission to publication for all publications in the volume\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003eAnnotation and post-publication comment\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe journal platform permits readers to leave comments and in-browser annotations via \u003ca href=\"https://web.hypothes.is/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003ehypothes.is\u003c/a\u003e. Readers will require a \u003ca href=\"https://web.hypothes.is/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003ehypothes.is\u003c/a\u003e account to create annotations, and have the option to make these public or private. Comments may be moderated by the journal, however, if they are non-offensive and relevant to the publication subject, comments will remain online without edit.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003eBecoming a Reviewer\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTo be added to the list of peer reviewers for the \u003cem\u003eInternational Journal of Integrated Care\u003c/em\u003e, please \u003ca href=\"https://account.ijic.org/index.php/up-j-ijic/user/register?source=\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eregister as a user\u003c/a\u003e. The registration form will allow you to indicate your areas of expertise and institutional affiliations. Please include as much information as you can to allow editors to assign appropriate review tasks, should your services be needed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003eAdvertisement Policy\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe journal only displays advertisements that are of relevance to its scope and will be of interest to the readership (e.g. upcoming conferences). All advertising space is provided free of charge and the editor and publisher have the right to decline or withdraw adverts at any point. Adverts will include a text heading to make it clear that they are adverts not related to the journal.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf you wish to propose a potential advert then please contact the \u003ca href=\"https://ijic.org/contact\"\u003eeditorial team\u003c/a\u003e. All advert images will have to be provided to the publisher.\u003c/p\u003e"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"b8:T1e9a,"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eThe peer review form is available on the following page. You can also upload additional files containing further comments relevant to the review on this page.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eBy accepting this invitation to review this article, you are agreeing to adhere to the Committee of Publication Ethics (COPE) guidelines for peer reviewers, which can be accessed at the following link: \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://doi.org/10.24318/cope.2019.1.9\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003ehttps://doi.org/10.24318/cope.2019.1.9\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eAs part of this review task, the journal expects:\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eAll correspondence and associated files/data linked to this submission must remain confidential, unless otherwise authorised by the journal.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eThe use of open Artificial Intelligence (AI) models - e.g. ChatGPT - are prohibited when completing the peer review, due to concerns over the sharing of data that is not publicly available. ​​Local models which do not upload information back into training datasets, or self-built models, are permitted to help guide the peer reviewer, however, the reviewer takes responsibility for the review feedback provided and will be accountable for the content that they submit. The reviewer must not rely on AI in regard to their opinion of the article and recommendation to the editor. See our full \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://ubiquitypress.com/site/ai-policy/\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eAI policy\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003e for further guidance.\u0026nbsp;\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eShould you require any assistance during the review the below may be of use. If not, please get in touch and we will be happy to help:\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://bit.ly/Reviewer-Guide-OJS-3\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003ehttps://bit.ly/Reviewer-Guide-OJS-3\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003e (downloadable PDF)\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://help.u-community.io\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003ehttps://help.u-community.io\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003e (online Help Center)\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGeneral guidance for the review:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eAll reviews should be provided in a courteous and respectful format. Whilst criticism of the content is part of the remit, such feedback should be written in a constructive and informed manner. The tone and language used in review feedback should be considered and provided in a collegial manner. Unsuitable content (aggressive, offensive, libellous, accusatory, discriminatory etc) comments will not be accepted. If part of a review report is deemed to be unsuitable, or require clarification, then the editor may, in very rare circumstances, choose to edit the report prior to showing the authors. Should this occur, only issues of tone, language and deviations from journal policy will be edited. They will not change the meaning or intention of the review, nor alter the reviewer\u0026rsquo;s professional opinion about the quality, content, or intellectual validity of the manuscript under review. Less extreme cases may simply warrant a cautionary note from the Editor in the decision letter. We greatly value the efforts that all our reviewers put into the journal. Writing reports that are constructive, courteous, and clear help give them maximum value.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003e________________________________________________________________________________________________________________\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003eBelow please find questions to consider for selected article types.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eResearch and Theory papers\u003c/strong\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e1. Is the problem the article tackles a significant one? \u003cbr /\u003e2. Does the paper present significant new interpretations or findings \u003cspan style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"\u003ein the field of integrated care \u003cbr /\u003e\u003c/span\u003e3. What are the deficiencies in the authors treatment (logical, methodological, statistical, clarity)? \u003cbr /\u003e4. If you recommend publication, can you suggest passages that need revision, reduction, deletion or expansion?.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eQuantitative research checklist\u003c/em\u003e \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e1. Was a power analysis performed? \u003cbr /\u003e2. Was a method of randomization performed? \u003cbr /\u003e3. Did a medical ethics committee assess the study protocol? \u003cbr /\u003e4. Were the groups similar at baseline in regards to the most important prognostic indicators? \u003cbr /\u003e5. Were the eligibility criteria specified adequately? \u003cbr /\u003e6. Were the operational definitions of outcomes valid? \u003cbr /\u003e7. Were the statistical tests appropriate to the data? \u003cbr /\u003e8. Were potential confounders controlled in the study design (for example matching) or statistical analysis (multivariate analysis)? \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThe appraisal of the overall methodological quality should be based on a weighted score in which the 1) similarity of groups at baseline, 2) randomization and 3) adequate statistical methods are assigned \u003cspan style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"\u003ethree\u003c/span\u003e points; the use of 4) power analysis and 5) control of confounders are assigned \u003cspan style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"\u003etwo\u003c/span\u003e points; and 6) assessment by a medical ethics committee, 7) unbiased outcome measure and 8) eligibility criteria are assigned \u003cspan style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"\u003eone\u003c/span\u003e point. The overall quality scores (QS) for each study should be calculated by summing up the score-weighted \u003cem\u003e\u003cspan style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"\u003eyes\u003c/span\u003e scores. \u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eQualitative research checklist\u003c/em\u003e \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e1. Was the research question clearly defined? \u003cbr /\u003e2. Overall, did the researcher make explicit in the account the theoretical framework and methods used at every stage of the research? \u003cbr /\u003e3. Was the context clearly described? \u003cbr /\u003e4. Was the sampling strategy/selection of cases described and justified? \u003cbr /\u003e5. Was the fieldwork described in detail? \u003cbr /\u003e6. Were the procedures for data analysis clearly described and theoretically justified? \u003cbr /\u003e7. Was the analysis repeated by more than one researcher to ensure reliability?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eIntegrated Care Cases\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e1. Is the problem the article describes a significant one? \u003cbr /\u003e2. Is the Integrated Care Case the paper describes relevant to the problem? \u003cbr /\u003e3. Is the Integrated Care Case the paper describes new to the readers of IJIC? \u003cbr /\u003e4. Is the Integrated Care Case presented in the paper clearly described? \u003cbr /\u003e5. Is the analysis of the Integrated Care Case based upon relevant argumentation? \u003cbr /\u003e6. Is the conclusion fitting to what has been shown in the foregoing description and analysis \u003cbr /\u003e7. Do the recommendations make sense for health professionals and organizations, informal carers and policy makers? \u003cbr /\u003e8. Does the paper offer a significant contribution to the field of \u003cspan style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"\u003eintegrated care delivery and policy\u003c/span\u003e?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePolicy Papers\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e1. Is the problem the article describes a significant one? \u003cbr /\u003e2. Is the policy development the paper describes relevant to the problem? \u003cbr /\u003e3. Is the policy development presented in the paper clearly described? \u003cbr /\u003e4. Is the analysis of the policy development based upon relevant argumentation? \u003cbr /\u003e5. Is the conclusion fitting to what has been shown in the foregoing analysis? \u003cbr /\u003e6. Do the recommendations make sense for policy makers? \u003cbr /\u003e7. Does the paper offer a significant contribution to the field of integrated care policy? \u003cbr /\u003e8. Please provide any comments for your judgements above.\u003c/p\u003e"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"b9:T66c,"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"\u003cp\u003ePeople-centred care seeks to build the skills and resources that individuals and communities need to be articulate and empowered users of health services. It is an approach that seeks to support people to make effective decisions about their own health to achieve the outcomes that matter most to them. It enables communities to become active in partnering with care services and contributing to relevant research, education and healthy public policy.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\r \r This Special Collection on \u003cem\u003ePeople-Driven Care: Co-Designing for Health and Wellbeing with Individuals and Communities\u003c/em\u003e was commissioned in 2020 to bring together knowledge and evidence of the potential impact of people-driven care, specifically to describe approaches focusing on empowering and engaging people and the role and impact of co-production and co-design.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\r \r The Special Collection demonstrates that that state of the evidence on the nature and impact of co-design and co-production in integrated care is limited, and that the rhetoric supporting people-centred care is not yet being matched by the reality of service delivery. Despite this, there is emerging evidence from the Special Collection to suggest that where care services are more people-driven  for example, through employing goal-oriented care  then services are potentially better coordinated around peoples needs as a result.\r \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\r \u003cb\u003eGuest editors:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\r \r Nicholas Goodwin, Suzanne Bethge, Anna-Sophia Bilgeri, Anthony Brown, Lourdes Ferrer, Jodeme Goldhar, Hannah Johnson, Robert Johnstone, Robin Miller, Susan Sheridan, Viktoria Stein, Danny Vadasz, Susan Royer\u003c/p\u003e"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"ba:T4d3,\u003cp\u003eThis 20th Anniversary Edition presents a series of policy papers which review progress with integrated care from countries and regions from across the world. To introduce the article, lead authors have provided a talking head of the main achievements and points of learning for other health and care systems.\u003c/p\u003e\r \u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://vimeo.com/showcase/8880019\" target=\"blank\"\u003e\r View the full collection of videos\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\r \r England: \u003ca href=\"https://vimeo.com/649622644\" target=\"blank\"\u003evimeo.com/649622644\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\r Scotland: \u003ca href=\"https://vimeo.com/610886115\"target=\"blank\"\u003evimeo.com/610886115\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\r Belgium: \u003ca href=\"https://vimeo.com/637137881\"target=\"blank\"\u003evimeo.com/637137881\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\r USA: \u003ca href=\"https://vimeo.com/617764256\"target=\"blank\"\u003evimeo.com/617764256\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\r Switzerland: \u003ca href=\"https://vimeo.com/617887149\"target=\"blank\"\u003evimeo.com/617887149\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eCanada: \u003ca href=\"https://vimeo.com/643616528\"target=\"blank\"\u003evimeo.com/643616528\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"https://vimeo.com/643619424\" target=\"blank\"\u003evimeo.com/643619424\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\r \r This collection was published as a full issue in Volume 21: \u003ca href=\"https://www.ijic.org/156/volume/21/issue/S2/\" target=\"blank\"\u003ewww.ijic.org/156/volume/21/issue/S2\u003c/a\u003ebb:T5f3,"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"\u003cp\u003eHealthy Homes and Neighbourhoods is an Australian integrated health and social care initiative for people, families and communities. Initially designed for families with children and young people, the project later expanded to offer an integrated health and social care approach for all peoples and their communities. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\r \r The project design arose from the critical realist translation of earlier social epidemiology research. Critical realist approaches were used not only to inform the research and design phase but also later implementation, evaluation, and sustained improvement cycles within Sydney Australia.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\r \r This special collection seeks to support the dissemination and learnings from the Project. The initial three papers describe the critical realist methodology used to translate an earlier social epidemiology research to an intervention design. That translation was undertaken in collaboration with local communities and interagency stakeholders. The evaluation protocol for Health Homes and Neighbourhoods is also described. That evaluation protocol seeks to apply a critical realist approach to the UK MRC advice on evaluation of complex interventions and methods drawn from both implementation and improvement science.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\r \r The work described here is also linked to four IFIC Special Interest Groups:\u003c/p\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\r Evidence-based Integrated Care\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\r Realist, Design and Evaluation\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\r Health and Social Care\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\r Children, Young People and their Families\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\r \r"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"bc:T5e2,"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"\u003cp\u003eProject INTEGRATE was a four-year EU-funded research project (September 2012 to August 2016) that aimed to gain valuable insights into the leadership, management and delivery of integrated care to support European care systems to respond to the challenges of ageing populations and the rise of people living with long-term chronic conditions (\u003ca href=\"http://projectintegrate.eu.com/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ehttp://projectintegrate.eu.com/\u003c/a\u003e) \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\r \r This special collection seeks to support the dissemination and learning from the Project by providing summaries and links to the published works of the academics involved, including to original papers published in IJIC. Specifically, the special collection focuses on the core work undertaken in the final phases of the research programme that investigated factors in the design, implementation, management and policy of integrated care programmes.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\r \r Involving an analysis of four European case studies of care integration, the research concluded that integrated care was an approach to service transformation that had the potential to improve the quality of care experiences and outcomes to patients. However, the research found that implementation was highly context-specific requiring a set of essential pre-requisites to be met at a micro-, meso- and macro-level.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\r \r Project INTEGRATE received funding from the EUs 7th Framework Programme for Research, Technical Development, and Demonstration Under Grant Agreement number 305821\u003c/p\u003e"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"bd:T58a,"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"Health and social care systems across the world are being challenged to meet the needs of an increasing number of people aging with multiple complex health and social needs. Integrated community based primary health care (ICBPHC) has been associated with better population level outcomes and lower system level costs and may be well suited to address the increasingly complex needs of populations; however implementation of ICBPHC faces many challenges. In this issue, we report on a large international research team collaborating to complete 9 interdisciplinary case studies, focused on the implementation of ICBPHC. The research team consists of patients and carers, clinicians, policymakers, and researchers. Exemplary cases of organizations that have successfully integrated CBPHC from Ontario, Quebec and New Zealand were studied using a mixed-method case study approach focusing on 4 analytic levels: Patient/carer, health care providers, organizations, and policies. The key question is What are the steps to implementing innovative integrated community-based primary health care models that address the health and social needs of older adults with complex care needs? and will be answered in three phases. The final output of the program will be a comprehensive guide to the design, implementation and scaling-up of innovative models of ICBPHC.\r \r Edited by Nick Goodwin, Tim Kenealy, and Walter P Wodchis"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"be:T586,"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"\u003cp\u003eThis collection of papers grows out of a collaborative project between IFIC and Edge Hill University (UK) that led to six webinars delivered by international experts on integrated care. The papers are original reflection pieces written especially for this collection by those who delivered the webinars in Spring and Summer 2016. They provide a unique summary of accumulated expertise in some of the most important themes in the integrated care field. This special collection also offers a good opportunity to reflect on progress and challenges in the field as care integration increasingly gains policy support and gathers momentum in many countries across the world.\u003c/p\u003e\r \r \u003c!--\u003cp\u003e\u003cb\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family: 'Source Sans Pro','helvetica neue', 'helvetica','Arial','sans-serif'; color: #46629E; font-size:'1rem'; font-weight:'600';\"\u003eEditorial\u003c/span\u003e\u003cbr/\u003e\r \u003cspan style=\"font-family: 'Source Sans Pro','helvetica neue', 'helvetica','Arial','sans-serif'; font-size:'1rem'; font-weight:'600';\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://www.ijic.org/articles/10.5334/ijic.2527/\"\u003eThe Building Blocks of Integrated Care\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr/\u003e\r \u003cspan style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\"\u003eAxel Kaehne\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e--\u003e\r \r \u003cp\u003eSee the Editorial: Kaehne, A 2016 The Building Blocks of Integrated Care. \u003ci\u003eInternational Journal of Integrated Care\u003c/i\u003e, 16(4): 5, pp. 12, DOI: \u003ca href=\"http://dx.doi.org/10.5334/ijic.2527\"\u003ehttp://dx.doi.org/10.5334/ijic.2527\u003c/a\u003e"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"bf:T4bf,\u003cp\u003eThe health and care workforce was under pressure long before the pandemic, not least because of new technologies, policy reforms and dwindling resources. In recent years, concepts like the Quadruple Aim or the WHO European Framework for Action for integrated health services delivery have helped to highlight the importance of workforce planning, education and training or role definitions for integrated care. If we want the principles of integrated care to become engrained in the work ethic and culture of health and care, a lot more needs to happen on many levels in order to ensure that the full potential of the individual and the concept as a whole can be fulfilled. When discussing the future of the integrated care workforce, therefore, it becomes apparent that a lot needs to change on many levels. However, knowledge and experience are still piecemeal in what needs to happen at which level and how the integrated care workforce should look like going forward. Who is part of this workforce and what do they need to succeed? This special collection seeks to bring together papers that explore all facets of an integrated care workforce.\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003eMore papers will be published over the coming weeks.\u003c/p\u003ec0:Ta2d,"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"\u003cp\u003eThe Scale-Up of Diabetes and Hypertension Care (SCUBY; https://www.scuby.eu/) project aimed to provide evidence on the scale-up of an \u003cstrong\u003e‘integrated care package’ (ICP) – \u003c/strong\u003ecomprising of (a) early detection and diagnosis, (b) treatment in primary care services, (c) health education, (d) self-management support to patients and caregivers, and (e) collaboration between caregivers – for T2D and HT, through the co-development and evaluation of roadmap-strategies.\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003eThe study was conducted in purposively selected types of health systems: a developing health system in a lower middle-income country (Cambodia); a centrally steered health system in a high-income country (Slovenia); and a publicly-funded highly privatized health-care health system in another high-income country (Belgium). A three-dimensional framework evaluates scale-up along three axes: (1) increase in population coverage; (2) expansion of the ICP; and (3) integration of the ICP into the health system referring to the degree to which governance arrangements, organization, financing, and service delivery allow the ICP to be adopted and diffused in the health system.\u003ca href=\"#_ftn1\" name=\"_ftnref1\"\u003e[1]\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003eThis \u003cstrong\u003ethematic issue\u003c/strong\u003e aims to provide guidance on scale-up of integrated care interventions for chronic diseases in varied contexts, based on evidence from the SCUBY experience. In this way, it shares valuable lessons for future integrated care interventions in other (but similar) contexts. The issue will address the following topics:\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003col\u003e\r\n\u003cli class=\"show\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e Editorial\u003c/strong\u003e with the rationale and concepts explained above\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli class=\"show\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e Scale-up of integrated care interventions in the current era\u003c/strong\u003e: What theories, methodologies and contemporary approaches are in use to scale-up intervention for research and implementation.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli class=\"show\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTaking stock of integrated care interventions for chronic diseases and challenges \u0026amp; opportunities for scale-up across contexts\u003c/strong\u003e. Scale-up processes and strategies: what are scale-up interventions, how do they work in practice and how can they be evaluated?\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ol\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e3: \u003cstrong\u003eResults of scale-up interventions\u003c/strong\u003e: Outcomes and impact: \u0026nbsp;Examples of impact evaluation studies\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"#_ftnref1\" name=\"_ftn1\"\u003e[1]\u003c/a\u003e Meessen et al., “From Scheme to System (Part 1): Notes on Conceptual and Methodological Innovations in the Multicountry Research Program on Scaling Up Results-Based Financing in Health Systems.”\u003c/p\u003e"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"b5:[\"$\",\"$Lb6\",null,{\"journal\":{\"title\":\"International Journal of Integrated Care\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"initials\":\"IJIC\",\"abbreviation\":\"Int J Integr Care\",\"description\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"p1\\\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\\\"s1\\\"\u003eThe \u003cem\u003eInternational Journal of Integrated Care\u003c/em\u003e (IJIC) is an online, open-access, peer-reviewed scientific journal that publishes original articles in the field of integrated care on a continuous basis.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\\n\u003cp class=\\\"p1\\\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\\\"s1\\\"\u003eIJIC has an Impact Factor of 2.60 (2024 JCR, received in June 2025)\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\\n\u003cp class=\\\"p1\\\"\u003eThe \u003ca href=\\\"/156/volume/21/issue/S2/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\"\u003eIJIC 20th Anniversary Issue\u003c/a\u003e was published in 2021.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"focus_scope\":\"$b7\",\"editorial_policies\":\"\",\"review_guidelines\":\"$b8\",\"archiving\":\"\",\"eissn\":\"1568-4156\",\"print_issn\":\"\",\"terms_conditions\":\"\",\"privacy_policy\":\"\u003cp\u003eThe names and email addresses entered in this journal site will be used exclusively for the stated purposes of this journal and will not be made available for any other purpose or to any other party. For more information, see the full Privacy Policy \u003ca href=\\\"/about/privacy-policy/\\\" target=\\\"blank\\\"\u003ehere\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eIJIC does not disclose or sell any personally identifiable information collected at this site to other companies or organisations. \u003cbr /\u003eWhen you enter IJIC for the first time we ask you to supply your title, name and email address. This enables us to contact you from time to time to draw your attention to information that may be of interest.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"published_by\":\"Ubiquity Press\",\"publisher_url\":\"http://www.ubiquitypress.com\",\"supported_submission_locales\":\"[\\\"en\\\"]\",\"cover\":{\"link\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-ijic-public/journals/1/journalCoverImage_en_US.jpg\",\"alt_text\":\"Cover Image\"},\"submission_disabled\":false,\"jpps_badge_enabled\":false,\"remove_journal_terminology\":false,\"accessibility_statement_link\":\"https://journals.support.ubiquity.pub/category/190-accessibility-statements\",\"jpps_path\":\"\",\"jol\":\"\",\"thumbnail\":{\"link\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-ijic-public/journals/1/journalThumbnail_en_US.jpg\",\"alt_text\":\"thumbnail image\"},\"favicon\":{\"link\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-ijic-public/journals/1/favicon_en_US.png\",\"alt_text\":\"ubiquity favicon\"},\"colors\":{\"primary\":\"#3E578E\",\"secondary\":\"#595959\"},\"google_analytics\":null,\"has_dois\":true,\"language\":{\"default_lang\":\"en\",\"supported\":[\"en\"],\"supported_submission_languages\":[\"en\"],\"locale_tag_style\":\"compact\"},\"sections\":[{\"name\":\"Research \u0026 theory\",\"id\":2,\"order\":5,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":true,\"only_editors\":false,\"text\":\"\u003cp\u003eResearch \u0026amp; theory (RT) papers include: original research; systematic reviews; new theoretical perspectives; and innovative research protocols (study designs).\u003c/p\u003e\\r\\n\u003cp\u003eTo improve the chance of acceptance of your manuscript, we recommend reading the specific\u0026nbsp;\u003ca href=\\\"https://account.ijic.org/index.php/up-j-ijic/libraryFiles/downloadPublic/9\\\"\u003eGuideline for Research \u0026amp; theory papers\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\",\"display\":true}},{\"name\":\"Integrated Care Cases\",\"id\":3,\"order\":4,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":true,\"only_editors\":false,\"text\":\"\u003cp\u003eIntegrated Care cases (ICC) are case studies of innovative local approaches to the delivery of integrated care in practice\u003c/p\u003e\\r\\n\u003cp\u003eTo improve the chance of acceptance of your manuscript, we recommend reading the specific\u0026nbsp;\u003ca href=\\\"https://account.ijic.org/index.php/up-j-ijic/libraryFiles/downloadPublic/11\\\"\u003eGuideline for Integrated Care Cases \u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\",\"display\":true}},{\"name\":\"Policy papers\",\"id\":4,\"order\":7,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":true,\"only_editors\":false,\"text\":\"\u003cp\u003ePolicy (P) papers\u0026nbsp;include: description and analysis of national and international policy developments on integrated care and their impact.\u003c/p\u003e\\r\\n\u003cp\u003eTo improve the chance of acceptance of your manuscript, we recommend reading the specific \u003ca href=\\\"https://account.ijic.org/index.php/up-j-ijic/libraryFiles/downloadPublic/12\\\"\u003eGuideline for Policy papers\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\",\"display\":true}},{\"name\":\"Correction\",\"id\":28,\"order\":16,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":false,\"only_editors\":true,\"text\":\"\",\"display\":false}},{\"name\":\"Editorials\",\"id\":6,\"order\":1,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":false,\"only_editors\":true,\"text\":\"\",\"display\":false}},{\"name\":\"Letter to the editor\",\"id\":7,\"order\":10,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":false,\"only_editors\":true,\"text\":\"\u003cp\u003eLetter to the editor (E) is a section for reactions to articles or editorials published in the IJIC. Contact the IJIC Managing Editor if you wish to submit a Letter to the editor.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"display\":false}},{\"name\":\"Poster Abstracts\",\"id\":17,\"order\":14,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":false,\"only_editors\":true,\"text\":\"\",\"display\":false}},{\"name\":\"Book Reviews\",\"id\":9,\"order\":9,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":false,\"only_editors\":true,\"text\":\"\u003cp\u003eBook reviews (BK) provide an outline of the main topics and a brief discussion of the strengths and weaknesses of the books, and their relevance for integrated care. Book Reviews are included in the journal on a range of relevant topics.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eTo improve the chance of acceptance of your manuscript, we recommend reading the specific \u003ca href=\\\"https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/ubiquity-partner-network/up/journal/ijic/IJIC-book-review-guideline.pdf\\\"\u003eGuideline for Books Reviews \u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\",\"display\":false}},{\"name\":\"Projects and Developments\",\"id\":10,\"order\":11,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":true,\"only_editors\":true,\"text\":\"\",\"display\":false}},{\"name\":\"PhD Thesis summaries\",\"id\":13,\"order\":2,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":false,\"only_editors\":false,\"text\":\"\u003cp\u003eThesis summaries (TS)\u0026nbsp;include the summation of the aims, theory, method, results and conclusions of PhD theses in integrated care.\u003c/p\u003e\\r\\n\u003cp\u003eTo improve the chance of acceptance of your manuscript, we recommend reading the specific \u003ca href=\\\"https://account.ijic.org/index.php/up-j-ijic/libraryFiles/downloadPublic/7\\\"\u003eGuideline for Thesis Summaries \u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\",\"display\":true}},{\"name\":\"Conference Abstracts\",\"id\":14,\"order\":13,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":false,\"only_editors\":true,\"text\":\"\",\"display\":false}},{\"name\":\"Keynote Abstracts\",\"id\":15,\"order\":12,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":false,\"only_editors\":true,\"text\":\"\",\"display\":false}},{\"name\":\"Lost and Found\",\"id\":20,\"order\":8,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":true,\"only_editors\":false,\"text\":\"\u003cp\u003eLost and Found (LF) papers are retrospective assessments of the impact, legacy and lessons of significant historical innovations or research into integrated care.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eTo improve the chance of acceptance of your manuscript, we recommend reading the specific \u003ca href=\\\"https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/ubiquity-partner-network/up/journal/ijic/IJIC-lost-and-found-guidleines.pdf\\\"\u003eGuideline for Lost and Found papers\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\",\"display\":true}},{\"name\":\"Perspective papers\",\"id\":21,\"order\":3,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":true,\"only_editors\":false,\"text\":\"\u003cp\u003ePerspective papers (PP) are short papers from leading managers and professionals working at the 'coalface' of integrated care.\u003c/p\u003e\\r\\n\u003cp\u003eTo improve the chance of acceptance of your manuscript, we recommend reading the specific \u003ca href=\\\"https://account.ijic.org/index.php/up-j-ijic/libraryFiles/downloadPublic/8\\\"\u003eGuideline for Perspective papers \u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\",\"display\":true}},{\"name\":\"Methodology papers\",\"id\":27,\"order\":6,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":true,\"only_editors\":false,\"text\":\"\u003cp\u003eMethodology papers are study protocols or similar articles, explaining and discussing new or innovative ways of applying a methodology in the field of integrated care\u003c/p\u003e\\r\\n\u003cp\u003eTo improve the chance of acceptance of your manuscript, we recommend reading the specific \u003ca href=\\\"https://account.ijic.org/index.php/up-j-ijic/libraryFiles/downloadPublic/10\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\"\u003eGuidelines for Methodology Papers\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"display\":true}},{\"name\":\"Workshop Abstracts\",\"id\":25,\"order\":15,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":true,\"only_editors\":true,\"text\":\"\",\"display\":false}}],\"licenses\":{\"name\":\"\",\"code\":\"\",\"link\":\"\"},\"subject_taxonomy\":[],\"ojs_version\":\"3.4.0.10\",\"static_pages\":[]},\"collections\":[{\"description\":\"\u003cp\u003eThe Voluntary and Community Sector (VCS) incorporates charities, social enterprises, volunteer led groups and community organisations. Their role includes delivery of personal and clinical services, peer support and befriending, and advocacy and representation. The contribution of the VCS to integrated care is substantial and accentuated during the COVID 19 pandemic when the VCS sector provided vital practical and emotional support. The VCS experiences many challenges to being seen as equal partners within integrated care and there is partial evidence base to date. This special edition responds to this evidence gap through considering the role, contribution and impacts of the VCS.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"short_description\":\"\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\\\"color: windowtext; font-weight: normal;\\\"\u003eThis special issue considers the role, contribution, impacts and learning of the Voluntary and Community Sector within integrated care.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\",\"ordering\":\"datePublished-2\",\"name\":\"The role of the Voluntary \u0026 Community Sector within Integrated Care\",\"creation_date\":null,\"show\":true,\"cover_alt\":null,\"cover_link\":null,\"id\":18,\"editors\":[{\"first_name\":\"Susan\",\"last_name\":\"Royer\"}],\"path\":\"/voluntary-community-sector\",\"user_sorting\":0},{\"description\":\"$b9\",\"short_description\":\"This special collection examines people-driven care and the role and impact of engagement and empowerment, co-production and co-design strategies.\",\"ordering\":\"datePublished-2\",\"name\":\"People-Driven Care: Co-designing for Health and Wellbeing with Individuals and Communities\",\"creation_date\":\"2022-12-30T00:00:00+00:00\",\"show\":true,\"cover_alt\":null,\"cover_link\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-ijic-public/journals/1/categories/7-category.png\",\"id\":7,\"editors\":[{\"first_name\":\"Susan\",\"last_name\":\"Royer\"}],\"path\":\"people-driven-care-co-designing-for-health-and-wellbeing-with-individuals-and-communities\",\"user_sorting\":1},{\"description\":\"$ba\",\"short_description\":\"This 20th Anniversary Edition presents a series of policy papers which review progress with integrated care from countries and regions from across the world. To introduce the article, lead authors have provided a talking head of the main achievements and points of learning for other health and care systems.\",\"ordering\":\"datePublished-2\",\"name\":\"IJIC 20th Anniversary Issue\",\"creation_date\":\"2021-10-29T00:00:00+00:00\",\"show\":true,\"cover_alt\":null,\"cover_link\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-ijic-public/journals/1/categories/6-category.png\",\"id\":6,\"editors\":[],\"path\":\"ijic-20th-anniversary-issue\",\"user_sorting\":2},{\"description\":\"\u003cp\u003eIn 2019, we finalized a four-year EU-funded research project on integrated care for older people called SUSTAIN. The SUSTAIN project was designed to support the development of integrated care for older people living at home with health and social care needs. Its objectives were twofold:\u003c/p\u003e\u003col\u003e\u003cli\u003e1. To support and monitor improvements to established integrated care initiatives and \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e2. To contribute to the adoption and application of such improvements to other health and social care systems and regions in Europe.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp\u003e The project has generated lots of insights into and experiences with integrated care implementation and evaluation. This special IJIC issue on SUSTAIN features six papers based on these lessons learned, covering a variety of aspects of integrated care, including the implementation of activities to improve integrated care, the exploration of experiences of different stakeholders with integrated care, and the evaluation of integrated care. \u003c/p\u003e\",\"short_description\":\"\u003cp\u003eThe SUSTAIN research project has generated lots of experiences with integrated care implementation and evaluation. This special issue features these lessons learned.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"ordering\":\"datePublished-2\",\"name\":\"Different contexts, similar challenges. SUSTAINs experiences with improving integrated care in Europe.\",\"creation_date\":\"2020-06-26T00:00:00+00:00\",\"show\":true,\"cover_alt\":null,\"cover_link\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-ijic-public/journals/1/categories/5-category.png\",\"id\":5,\"editors\":[],\"path\":\"different-contexts-similar-challenges-sustain-s-experiences-with-improving-integrated-care-in-europe\",\"user_sorting\":3},{\"description\":\"$bb\",\"short_description\":\"\u003cp\u003eThis special collection presents a realist approach to translating social epidemiological research to health and social care integrated care initiatives.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"ordering\":\"datePublished-2\",\"name\":\"The Healthy Homes and Neighbourhoods integrated health and social care initiative\",\"creation_date\":\"2019-07-25T00:00:00+00:00\",\"show\":true,\"cover_alt\":null,\"cover_link\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-ijic-public/journals/1/categories/4-category.jpg\",\"id\":4,\"editors\":[{\"first_name\":\"Susan\",\"last_name\":\"Royer\"}],\"path\":\"the-healthy-homes-and-neighbourhoods-integrated-health-and-social-care-initiative\",\"user_sorting\":4},{\"description\":\"$bc\",\"short_description\":\"This special collection brings together summaries of published works by the academics involved in the EU research Project INTEGRATE\",\"ordering\":\"datePublished-2\",\"name\":\"Project INTEGRATE: Lessons for Policy, Management and Implementation of Integrated Care in Europe\",\"creation_date\":\"2017-09-13T00:00:00+00:00\",\"show\":true,\"cover_alt\":null,\"cover_link\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-ijic-public/journals/1/categories/3-category.png\",\"id\":3,\"editors\":[{\"first_name\":\"Susan\",\"last_name\":\"Royer\"}],\"path\":\"project-integrate-lessons-for-policy-management-and-implementation-of-integrated-care-in-europe\",\"user_sorting\":5},{\"description\":\"$bd\",\"short_description\":\"This special collection from the iCOACH project presents its research on implementing integrated care to older adults with complex needs.\",\"ordering\":\"datePublished-2\",\"name\":\"iCOACH. Implementing Integrated Care for Older Adults with Complex Health Needs\",\"creation_date\":\"2017-06-27T00:00:00+00:00\",\"show\":true,\"cover_alt\":null,\"cover_link\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-ijic-public/journals/1/categories/2-category.jpg\",\"id\":2,\"editors\":[{\"first_name\":\"Susan\",\"last_name\":\"Royer\"}],\"path\":\"icoach\",\"user_sorting\":6},{\"description\":\"$be\",\"short_description\":\"\u003cp\u003eCollection of papers originating in a webinar series on integrated care produced by IFIC and Edge Hill University (UK).\u003c/p\u003e\",\"ordering\":\"datePublished-2\",\"name\":\"The Building Blocks of Integrated Care\",\"creation_date\":\"2016-10-28T00:00:00+00:00\",\"show\":true,\"cover_alt\":null,\"cover_link\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-ijic-public/journals/1/categories/1-category.jpg\",\"id\":1,\"editors\":[],\"path\":\"the-building-blocks-of-integrated-care\",\"user_sorting\":7},{\"description\":\"$bf\",\"short_description\":\"\u003cp\u003eThis special collection seeks to bring together papers that explore all facets of an integrated care workforce.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"ordering\":\"datePublished-1\",\"name\":\"The Integrated Care Workforce: What does it need? Who does it take?\",\"creation_date\":\"2023-05-16T00:00:00+00:00\",\"show\":true,\"cover_alt\":\"\",\"cover_link\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-ijic-public/journals/1/categories/15_category-cover_en_US.png\",\"id\":15,\"editors\":[{\"first_name\":\"Susan\",\"last_name\":\"Royer\"}],\"path\":\"the-integrated-care-workforce\",\"user_sorting\":8},{\"description\":\"$c0\",\"short_description\":\"\u003cp\u003eWe aim to provide guidance on scale-up of integrated chronic disease care in varied contexts, based on the SCUBY experience.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"ordering\":\"datePublished-1\",\"name\":\"Scale-up of Integrated Care Interventions for Chronic Diseases in Diverse Settings - Experiences from the Scale-up Integrated Care for Diabetes and Hypertension (SCUBY) Project\",\"creation_date\":null,\"show\":true,\"cover_alt\":\"\",\"cover_link\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-ijic-public/journals/1/categories/17_category-cover_en_US.png\",\"id\":17,\"editors\":[],\"path\":\"/scuby\",\"user_sorting\":10}],\"total\":8971,\"query\":{\"page\":1,\"items\":25,\"collection\":\"$undefined\",\"taxonomy\":\"$undefined\",\"section\":\"$undefined\"}}]\n"])</script></body></html>